Text.Value: Aw, is the little kitten afraid of some shadows? PATHETIC!
I do not seek your territory, noble beast, only a few moments of your time.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Indicates paws by gesturing with head or raising claws, whatever we can manage.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Cat] rears back defensive and swipes at player <Greg>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The cat rears back in a defensive stance and hisses at the player, maybe even swipes paws if it's possibe.

Text.Value: You should get out of here - this place is vulnerable to the shadow curse.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The cat doesn't approach, but meows in a non-threatening (though still wary) way

Text.Value: Barcus is permitted and I'm not?
Quite the specimen you are. How did you come to this place?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: DU player hisses or growls at the cat horribly.

Text.Value: Good of you to notice. For my part, I have noticed the cleric is a liar.
My intentions are pure. I only wanted to admire you up close.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Cat] lunges and swipe at player, [Player] backs off when cat attacks <LiliT>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The cat lunges out and swipes at the player's foot. Player steps back, but isn't hurt.
Can in a some aggressive idle (arched back)

Text.Value: Well, at least you purr for me...
I don't know who you are. I don't know why you're here. But I will kill you.
I see. Yes, perhaps you're right.
Plenty of pointless banging about. The only highlight was when the cleric here promised me a bit of milk that has yet to materialise.
How did you get to this place?
*Your years of hunting and tracking have taught you to recognise a territorial animal when you see it.*
She promised me a bit of milk. But do you see any milk? Do you? Nor do I. Disgraceful.
Indeed, you will. Or you'll find my claws planted firmly in your dangles.

EditorData.stateContext: Player is crouching in a 'here kitty' fashion

Text.Value: Easy, kitty. I mean you no harm.
What's got your whiskers in a twist?
You're in my territory. Get out.
Good. I'd like it if we could have a civil discussion.
This is my territory. And you're in it.
Try to muster some kindness, and calm the creature.
You'll be under attack if you don't heed my hiss!
Would that I lived on an island, far away, all alone...
Chk. Why would anyone keep such neurotic creatures as pets?
You've had enough! Now go! Quickly! HISS!
AND YET YOU HARM ME BY YOUR VERY PRESENCE!
I could use someone like you in my camp. Care to join?

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Player] crouches and holds hand out "here kitty kitty" idling crouch <Greg>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player crouches down on haunches and holds out hand in a 'here kitty kitty' way

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Cat] meows unfriendly, ignore and walks away <LiliT>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Cat meows in an unfriendly way and backs away, disengaging with player.

Text.Value: A parting piece of advice: don't trust the cleric. She's a bounder and a cad. Much like yourself, some might say.
You seem like someone who knows what he's about. Heard anything interesting around here?
There you are, unfortunately. Ever since you arrived, things keep... changing. I hate it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Angry cat noise leading to end of dialogue

Text.Value: You know, I think it's time I move somewhere better-suited to my lifestyle.

Synopsis: Cat is hanging around Barcus' workshop. Cat is not very friendly and player won't really be able to change the cat into being friendly, only temporarily not-aggro. If the player intimidates the cat, they can convince the cat to leave into the shadowcurse. Might do followup in future but none planned now. If placated, cat will tell player not to trust Isobel.
